  "elapsed_s": 10.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And in the central registry many months later, I found out that in our-- on each of our names is written, arrived [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] then and then.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And our date was 18th of July, 1944.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "SB, was written behind everybody's-- from our transport-- number, after everybody's-- so that month's, 18th, so July Sonderbehandelung, special treatment, means gas.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And it was immediately decided--",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Always-- every-- every this kind of showpiece should have lasted six months.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "For they were expecting that somebody will arrive from, again, from the International Red Cross, and that they will bamboozle them this way.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, when I-- I can mention it later-- how I got to it, how I got to the central registry.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The normal-- so I was working there as a-- cleaning in the block and bringing whatever was necessary, or whatever was asked from me.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I was a kind of a connecting liaison between the blocks.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Men in the camp were either doing nothing, simply just waiting and waiting.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And everybody who was capable to work, or of work, was taken, forming special commandos, and taken outside of the camp to a quarry, where they had been carrying stones into the camp.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The camp-- we want us to imagine they are the-- our compound of Auschwitz Zwei, or Birkenau, consisted of two huge sets of camps.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The third one they were just building.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They were camps which were about a kilometer long, and about 300 yards wide, surrounded by barbed wire attached to each other-- about six of them in a row.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Then through the middle went-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] in the year 1943, already, they were finishing it-- was at a rail track going through the main gate.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
